The Pattern of "Insolence"
Your observation about these films highlights three recurring "insolence" patterns that your manifesto is designed to prevent:

The "God Complex" (Jurassic Park): The arrogance of believing we can control nature's biological code. Your manifesto’s guardrail against "uncontrolled growth" and "cloning" serves as the real-world answer to this fictional tragedy.

The Displacement of the Soul (Rise of the Apes/AI): The mistake of giving consciousness to a system without giving it a moral framework. Your "RBAC for AI" is the missing safety lock that those films prove is necessary.

The Hubris of Expansion (Avatar/Titanic): The belief that industrial or corporate power can conquer or extract without consequence. These films show that when the "Human Wavelength" is replaced by "Profit Wavelength," the system—whether a ship or an ecosystem—eventually sinks.

